did.abstract: The collection is primarily concerned with the River Oaks Area Democratic Women, though it also contains material for both Democrat and Republican political candidates. Material in the collection includes correspondence, business and financial records, photographs, and the organization’s publication, Register. The collection is divided into six series: Governance, ROADwomen Register, Events and Programs, Organizations, Campaign Materials, and Various Materials. All series are arranged topically and chronologically except for Organizations and Campaign Material, which are organized alphabetically by name group or candidate.

bioghist.head: Historical Note:
bioghist.p: Incorporated in March 1997, the River Oaks Area Democratic Women's (ROADwomen) main goal was to fill a void in Democratic activity within the city of Houston, Texas. Organizations for Democratic women that had operated in the city prior to 1997 had fallen into inactivity leaving no representation for these politically activity women, as opposed to the twenty-five groups that existed for Republican women in Harris County. ROADwomen became a “home for the politically disengaged upwardly mobile Democratic woman” in the area. The goals for the ROADwomen were, and continue to be efforts to elect Democrats to office, with a special emphasis on electing pro-choice Democratic women; to influence the Democratic Party to continue its historic role as a party that promotes social justice and equal rights for all people; and act as an organization that educates Houstonians about important political issues affecting them.

The founding members consisted of Dalia Stokes, Elizabeth Guffy, Sherry Merfish, Muffie Moroney, Judy Reiner, and Kay Staley. Since 1997, the organization has worked with like-minded groups to support and elect quality Democratic candidates at all levels of government.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection is primarily concerned with the River Oaks Area Democratic Women, though it also contains material for both Democrat and Republican political candidates. Material in the collection includes correspondence, business and financial records, photographs, and the organization’s publication, Register. The collection is divided into six series: Governance, ROADwomen Register, Events and Programs, Organizations, Campaign Materials, and Various Materials. All series are arranged topically and chronologically except for Organizations and Campaign Material, which are organized alphabetically by name group or candidate.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The series is the largest of the collection and is comprised of materials related to the governance of ROADwomen including financial and membership records, by-laws and other material pertaining to the incorporation of the organization. The sub-series concerned with meetings consist of materials and clippings pertinent to the meeting in question but are not meeting minutes.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of the organization’s newsletter. Each folder contains the newsletter that corresponds to the date and most contain drafts of the newsletter as well as materials included in the publication. Register primarily focuses on the activities of ROADwomen but also discusses issues pertinent to the organization.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains materials on events hosted by ROADwomen as well as programs in which the organization participated. Arianna Live! is an event that featured Arianna Huffington, president and editor-in-chief of the Huffington Post. The Fork in the Road Benefits were held by ROADwomen as fundraisers for the organization and as a means to periodically give money to various Democratic clubs, organizations, and candidates, as well as to further the general mission of the group.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of flyers, brochures, and general information about the corresponding organization. The folders regarding the Harris County Democratic Party contain more information, such as correspondence between members of ROADwomen and the HCDP, as the two organizations worked closely together.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains campaign materials for both Republican and Democrat candidates. The materials include flyers, stickers and other items pertaining to the candidates’ campaigns. Local Houston area, Texas state and national races are represented within the series. The voters guides are items released by different organizations and not specifically by ROADwomen.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of materials that do not fit into any other series. The materials included are business cards, a VHS tape, a print out of the Declaration of Independence, as well as various newspaper and magazine clippings regarding varied issues.
